.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual-testing-playbook/cli-hooks-and-plugin/skill-advisor-cli-fallback.md:21:This scenario validates the 028 CLI fallback for the advisor daemon. `node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs` exposes 9 commands with byte-identical schemas to `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, sends calls untrusted by default behind a fail-closed trusted-mutation gate, and shares the program exit taxonomy 0/1/64/69/75. All checks below run against a sandboxed socket directory and refuse-before-IPC paths, so host daemons are never contacted and nothing is spawned.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual-testing-playbook/cli-hooks-and-plugin/skill-advisor-cli-fallback.md:43:node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs list-tools --format json \
