.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/manual-testing-playbook/multi-provider/variant-levels-comparison.md:53:For full-spectrum validation on a provider whose full range is verified, run the low/medium/high/xhigh sweep against `openai/gpt-5.6-sol` and confirm byte counts increase monotonically. This catches regressions where two adjacent variants produce identical responses (effectively halving the operator's tuning surface). Per-provider variant ranges to exercise (sourced from `references/cli-reference.md` §5, current as of this skill's v1.3.17 baseline — re-verify against a live `opencode run --help` before relying on an unlisted value):
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/manual-testing-playbook/multi-provider/variant-levels-comparison.md:60:| `openai/gpt-5.6-sol` | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/`xhigh` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md:139:| `--model` | `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` | Direct DeepSeek is the default provider — elevated reasoning at low cost; operator may override (e.g. `deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash`, `kimi-for-coding/k2p7`, or any live OpenAI GPT-5.6 slug: `openai/gpt-5.6`, `openai/gpt-5.6-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-terra-pro`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `openai/gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md:185:| Default missing | 0 | **ASK user** before substituting (offer A: openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro, B: login deepseek and retry, C: name a different model) — do not dispatch until configured |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md:242:  A) Use `openai/gpt-5.6-sol-pro --variant high` (OpenAI premium, configured now — paid)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/cli-reference.md:296:| `openai` GPT-5.6 (`gpt-5.6` / `gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) | `--variant` maps to OpenAI reasoning effort — a separate lever from the model tier: `none`/`low`/`medium`/`high`/**`xhigh`** (Pro tiers — `gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`: `medium`/`high`/`xhigh` — **inferred from the now-retired `gpt-5.5-pro` mapping and unverified against the live catalog (which no longer lists `gpt-5.5-pro` to re-check); smoke-test a Pro slug at `--variant low` before relying on the restriction**). **The `-fast` slugs** (`gpt-5.6-fast` / `gpt-5.6-sol-fast` / `gpt-5.6-terra-fast` / `gpt-5.6-luna-fast`) are the low-latency **Fast** model tier (OpenAI `priority` service tier) with the same effort range — e.g. `--model openai/gpt-5.6-sol-fast --variant xhigh`. `gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default; confirm live slugs via `opencode models openai`. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/references/destructive-scope-violations.md:142:The 2026-05-04 incident was specifically observed with `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` under `/deep:review:auto`. Until a runtime scope guard ships (see §5), the cross-phase synthesis recommendation stands: **for multi-phase deep-review work, prefer `cli-copilot` with `gpt-5.6-sol --reasoning-effort high`** (verify `gpt-5.6-sol` availability on the Copilot surface — this slug is carried over from a gpt-5.5-era Copilot-catalog check and is NOT re-verified; `opencode models openai` does not cover Copilot. If Copilot does not expose it, pick an available Copilot model rather than silently falling back to the risky default) when available, and fall back to deepseek only with Layers 1+2+3 all in place. Memory feedback `feedback_copilot_concurrency_override.md` caps Copilot at 3 parallel dispatches; sequence the work accordingly.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.3.md:4:**Status**: Content-hygiene fix. Reconciles a pkill safety self-contradiction, removes a stale retired-skill table row, adds a missing share-confirmation note, aligns the default-dispatch recipe with the no-top-level-`--agent` contract, and repairs 6 corrupted manual-testing-playbook filename links. No model-roster or provider changes; builds on top of v1.3.15.2's GPT-5.6 rename (not a revert).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.3.md:10:Five real content bugs surfaced by the whole-program deep review (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/125-cli-external-parent/review/review-report.md` §3 WS-A, plus a Fable-5 finding A-P1-3) are fixed. All five are pre-existing content bugs — none were caused by the v1.3.15.2 GPT-5.6 rename.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.3.md:50:- v1.3.15.2's GPT-5.6 model-roster rename (bare tier + Sol/Terra/Luna families, `gpt-5.6-sol` flagship default) is untouched — this entry builds on top of it, not a revert.
