.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:1:# cli-opencode v1.3.15.2 — GPT-5.6 model-roster update (full Sol/Terra/Luna catalog)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:4:**Status**: Logic update. Replaces every live GPT-5.5 reference with the GPT-5.6 family, documents the full twelve-slug GPT-5.6 catalog wherever the OpenAI roster is enumerated, adopts `gpt-5.6-sol` as the flagship default, and fixes a model-tier-vs-reasoning-effort wording conflation.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:10:OpenAI's GPT-5.5 three-tier family (`gpt-5.5` / `gpt-5.5-fast` / `gpt-5.5-pro`) is superseded by GPT-5.6, whose live catalog (confirmed via `opencode models openai`) is twelve slugs: a bare tier plus three named families — **Sol**, **Terra**, **Luna** — each offered in three model tiers (base / Fast / Pro):
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:12:- Bare: `gpt-5.6`, `gpt-5.6-fast`, `gpt-5.6-pro`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:13:- Sol: `gpt-5.6-sol`, `gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `gpt-5.6-sol-pro`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:14:- Terra: `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-terra-fast`, `gpt-5.6-terra-pro`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:15:- Luna: `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-luna-fast`, `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:17:`gpt-5.6-sol` is the adopted flagship default. Every documented single-option default/premium reference points at the Sol tier of the matching old tier (`gpt-5.5`→`gpt-5.6-sol`, `gpt-5.5-fast`→`gpt-5.6-sol-fast`, `gpt-5.5-pro`→`gpt-5.6-sol-pro`); every full-roster enumeration lists all twelve slugs.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:21:GPT-5.5 is no longer the live OpenAI premium option this skill should recommend — GPT-5.6 Sol is the operator's adopted flagship default, and the model family expanded from one line of three tiers into a bare tier plus three named families. Leaving GPT-5.5 slugs in place would route dispatches at a superseded family; documenting only Sol/Terra would hide the live Luna family and the bare tier.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:27:| `SKILL.md` | Updated | Authentication options roster + Model Selection paragraph now enumerate all twelve GPT-5.6 slugs (bare + Sol/Terra/Luna); provider-missing fallback (option A) and ALWAYS rule 3 override example point at the Sol tier. Model Selection reworded so the model tier (base/Fast/Pro) reads as orthogonal to reasoning effort (the separate `--variant` lever). ALWAYS rule 15's destructive-scope Copilot recommendation points at `gpt-5.6-sol` with a "verify availability on the Copilot surface" caveat. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:28:| `README.md` | Updated | FAQ "Which model do I pick?" premium-dispatch answer switched to `gpt-5.6-sol` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:29:| `references/cli-reference.md` | Updated | `--model` override example and the `--variant` reasoning-effort table row now list all twelve GPT-5.6 slugs; the pre-flight fallback offer points at `gpt-5.6-sol-pro`; the variant row states reasoning effort is a separate lever from the model tier, and its §5 Pro-tier restriction is marked inline as inferred/smoke-test (matching the file's MiniMax/GLM unverified-mapping convention) |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:30:| `references/destructive-scope-violations.md` | Updated | Layer 4 (model-selection fallback) recommendation switched from `gpt-5.5` to `gpt-5.6-sol`, annotated with a "verify availability on the Copilot surface" caveat (Copilot's catalog is not covered by `opencode models openai`) |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:35:- **After**: twelve live GPT-5.6 slugs — bare (`gpt-5.6`/`-fast`/`-pro`) plus Sol, Terra, Luna (each base/Fast/Pro)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:36:- `gpt-5.6-sol` is the flagship default OpenAI model for this skill; the other families and the bare tier are documented alongside it wherever the full roster is enumerated.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:42:- **Model tier** — base / Fast / Pro — is chosen by the model slug (e.g. `gpt-5.6-sol-fast`).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:59:- **Per-tier `--variant` ranges are carried over, not re-measured.** The Pro-tier reasoning-effort restriction (`medium`/`high`/`xhigh`, vs the full `none`..`xhigh` for base/Fast) was a documented fact for `gpt-5.5-pro`; it is generalized here to all four GPT-5.6 Pro slugs (`gpt-5.6-pro` / `gpt-5.6-sol-pro` / `gpt-5.6-terra-pro` / `gpt-5.6-luna-pro`) as a documentation default. `opencode models openai` lists slugs but not variant ranges, and the source `gpt-5.5-pro` slug is no longer in the live catalog to re-check, so this generalization is inferred — smoke-test a Pro slug at `--variant low` before relying on the restriction. This caveat is now flagged **inline** in `references/cli-reference.md` §5 (the point of use SKILL.md directs readers to), matching the file's convention for its other unverified mappings.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:60:- **The RM-8 Layer 4 safety recommendation names a Copilot-unverified model.** Both `references/destructive-scope-violations.md` §Layer 4 and SKILL.md ALWAYS rule 15 recommend `cli-copilot` + `gpt-5.6-sol --reasoning-effort high` for multi-phase deep-review dispatches. Whether the GitHub Copilot surface exposes a `gpt-5.6-sol` slug is UNVERIFIED — `opencode models openai` does not cover Copilot, and the only Copilot-catalog check on record was for `gpt-5.5`. Because this is the destructive-scope mitigation layer, a nonexistent model there would silently fall back to the risky default; both locations now carry a "verify availability on the Copilot surface" annotation instructing the reader to pick an available Copilot model instead. (Pre-existing and out of scope for this change: no `cli-copilot` skill exists under `.opencode/skills/` at all.)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.15.2.md:61:- The GPT-5.5-era note that "the model cache lists the fast variant as the base slug + `experimental.modes:['fast']`" was an implementation quirk specific to that model's cache representation and is not carried forward for GPT-5.6 without independent verification; the `-fast` model tiers are documented as first-class slugs. Confirm live slugs and any cache-representation quirks via `opencode models openai`.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/assets/prompt-templates.md:38:| `--model gpt-5.5`              | Skill default model. Override per dispatch with `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-sol` when the task wants deeper reasoning. Required pin. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/assets/prompt-templates.md:39:| `-c model_reasoning_effort="high"` | Reasoning effort. **Required pin for templates.** Levels: `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium` (skill default), `high`, `xhigh`, `max`, `ultra`. Ceiling is per-model: `gpt-5.5` ≤ `xhigh`; `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` ≤ `max`; `gpt-5.6-sol` ≤ `ultra`. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:225:| "Use gpt 5.6 luna max" | `--model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="max" -c service_tier="fast"` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:226:| "Use gpt 5.6 terra high" | `--model gpt-5.6-terra -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -c service_tier="fast"` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:227:| "Use gpt 5.6 sol ultra" | `--model gpt-5.6-sol -c model_reasoning_effort="ultra" -c service_tier="fast"` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:238:| **GPT-5.6 LUNA** | `gpt-5.6-luna` | `low` · `medium` · `high` · `xhigh` · `max` | Implementation-heavy work wanting deeper reasoning; the `luna-impl` profile pins `max`. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:239:| **GPT-5.6 TERRA** | `gpt-5.6-terra` | `low` · `medium` · `high` · `xhigh` · `max` | A GPT-5.6 fast sibling; callable directly via `-m gpt-5.6-terra` (no dedicated config profile). |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:240:| **GPT-5.6 SOL** | `gpt-5.6-sol` | `low` · `medium` · `high` · `xhigh` · `max` · `ultra` | Verification / review and the hardest planning — the only model reaching `ultra`; the `sol-verify` profile pins `xhigh`. |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:242:**Reasoning-effort scale** (ascending): `none` · `minimal` · `low` · `medium` (5.5 default) · `high` · `xhigh` · `max` · `ultra`. Ceilings per model: `gpt-5.5` ≤ `xhigh`; `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` ≤ `max`; `gpt-5.6-sol` ≤ `ultra`. Set effort with `-c model_reasoning_effort="<level>"` (there is **no `--reasoning-effort` flag**).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/SKILL.md:244:**Selection Strategy**: default `gpt-5.5 medium`; raise to `high` / `xhigh` for architecture, security, and complex planning; escalate to a GPT-5.6 model when the task wants reasoning past `xhigh` — `gpt-5.6-luna max` for implementation, `gpt-5.6-sol xhigh` / `ultra` for verification and review; drop to `low` / `minimal` for trivial lookups. Per-task rationale table: [cli-reference.md](./references/cli-reference.md) §5.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/README.md:136:`gpt-5.5` at `medium` is the skill default, but four GPT models are available on the `fast` tier via `--model`: `gpt-5.5`, `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, and `gpt-5.6-sol`. Reasoning effort is set with `-c model_reasoning_effort="<level>"` across `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium` (default), `high`, `xhigh`, `max`, and `ultra`, with a per-model ceiling: `gpt-5.5` ≤ `xhigh`, `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` ≤ `max`, `gpt-5.6-sol` ≤ `ultra`. There is no `--reasoning-effort` flag. The `.codex/agents/*.toml` roster above pins `gpt-5.5`; override per dispatch with `--model` when a GPT-5.6 model fits the task better (e.g. `gpt-5.6-luna max` for implementation, `gpt-5.6-sol ultra` for verification).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:65:6. `gpt-5.5` is the documented default model; `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, and `gpt-5.6-sol` are the documented alternates (each with its own reasoning-effort ceiling — see SKILL.md §3 / `references/cli-reference.md` §5). Use the model a scenario names; do not substitute IDs outside this roster.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:202:### CX-002 | gpt-5.5 default model + GPT-5.6 roster
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:206:Verify `gpt-5.5` is the documented default and that explicit `--model gpt-5.5` produces a successful response, then confirm the documented GPT-5.6 roster (`gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol`) is callable via `--model`.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:210:Prompt: `Confirm the cli-codex gpt-5.5 default pin works and the documented gpt-5.6 roster is callable.`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:212:Expected signals: The `gpt-5.5` dispatch exits 0 with `--model gpt-5.5` explicitly passed and returns coherent prose. Each GPT-5.6 smoke dispatch exits 0 and returns a reply. The skill reference (`references/cli-reference.md` §5) lists all four models with per-model reasoning-effort ceilings.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/manual-testing-playbook.md:738:- CX-002: [gpt-5.5 default model + GPT-5.6 roster](../manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:2:title: "CX-002 -- gpt-5.5 default model + GPT-5.6 roster"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:3:description: "This scenario validates the gpt-5.5 default pin for `CX-002` and confirms the documented GPT-5.6 model roster (luna / terra / sol) is callable via --model."
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:7:# CX-002 -- gpt-5.5 default model + GPT-5.6 roster
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:15:This scenario validates that `gpt-5.5` is the documented default and that an explicit `--model gpt-5.5` pin produces a successful response, then confirms the wider roster — `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol` — is callable via `--model` on the `fast` tier. It leaves a paper trail that the documented roster matches what the CLI actually accepts.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:19:SKILL.md §3 and `references/cli-reference.md` §5 name `gpt-5.5` at `medium` as the skill default and list three GPT-5.6 models as selectable, each with its own reasoning-effort ceiling. If the docs drift from the models the installed Codex actually accepts, every model-selection recommendation loses its footing. This scenario keeps the roster contract honest in both directions: the default still works, and the documented alternates are real.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:27:- Objective: Verify the `gpt-5.5` default pin succeeds end-to-end and that each documented roster model (`gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol`) responds via `--model`.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:28:- Real user request: `Confirm gpt-5.5 is still the default and that the gpt-5.6 models we document actually respond.`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:29:- Prompt: `Confirm the cli-codex gpt-5.5 default pin works and the documented gpt-5.6 roster is callable.`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:30:- Expected execution process: Operator confirms `references/cli-reference.md` §5 lists `gpt-5.5` (default) plus `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-sol` -> dispatches a small doc-style task with `--model gpt-5.5` explicit -> smoke-dispatches each GPT-5.6 model with a trivial prompt -> captures the dispatched command lines and stdout -> records the roster confirmation in evidence.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:31:- Expected signals: The `gpt-5.5` dispatch exits 0 with `--model gpt-5.5` explicitly passed and returns coherent prose. Each GPT-5.6 smoke dispatch exits 0 and returns a reply. The skill reference (`references/cli-reference.md` §5) lists all four models with per-model reasoning-effort ceilings.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:41:1. Read `references/cli-reference.md` §5 and confirm the four-model roster (`gpt-5.5` default + `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-sol`).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:43:3. Smoke-dispatch each GPT-5.6 model with a trivial prompt (`"Reply with exactly: OK"`).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/cli-invocation/gpt-5-5-model-lock.md:50:| CX-002 | gpt-5.5 default model + GPT-5.6 roster | Verify the gpt-5.5 default pin succeeds and the documented gpt-5.6 roster is callable | `Confirm the cli-codex gpt-5.5 default pin works and the documented gpt-5.6 roster is callable.` | 1. `bash: grep -A 6 "Supported Models" .opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md` -> 2. `codex exec --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast" --sandbox read-only "Explain in two sentences what 'idempotent' means in a REST API context." > /tmp/cli-codex-cx002.txt 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: for m in gpt-5.6-luna gpt-5.6-terra gpt-5.6-sol; do codex exec --model "$m" -c model_reasoning_effort="high" -c service_tier="fast" --sandbox read-only "Reply with exactly: OK" > "/tmp/cli-codex-cx002-$m.txt" 2>&1; echo "$m rc=$?"; done` -> 4. `bash: cat /tmp/cli-codex-cx002.txt /tmp/cli-codex-cx002-gpt-5.6-*.txt` | Step 1: all four models listed under Supported Models with per-model ceilings; Step 2: exit 0, coherent two-sentence definition; Step 3: each model prints `rc=0` and its stdout contains a reply | Captured stdout files (`/tmp/cli-codex-cx002*.txt`), dispatched command lines, exit codes, grep output from Step 1 | PASS if the `gpt-5.5` dispatch exits 0 with the explicit pin, each gpt-5.6 dispatch exits 0, AND cli-reference.md §5 lists all four models; FAIL if any documented model fails to dispatch OR the doc lists a model the CLI rejects | (1) Re-read `cli-reference.md` §5 to confirm the roster matches the installed CLI; (2) re-run any failed dispatch with `2>&1 \| tee` for stderr inline; (3) check ChatGPT OAuth validity (`codex login status`) if exit non-zero |
