.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:212:| `ultra` | Deepest reasoning — `gpt-5.6-sol` only | `gpt-5.6-sol` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:228:Always specify `--model` explicitly in scripts for predictability (`gpt-5.5` is the skill default); omitting it relies on the CLI default, which may change across versions. When a task wants reasoning past `xhigh`, escalate the model: `--model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="max"` for deep implementation, `--model gpt-5.6-sol -c model_reasoning_effort="ultra"` for the hardest verification/review.
