.opencode/specs/system-code-graph/035-rust-backend-rewrite/001-research/research/deep-research-strategy.md:3:> Charter the future deep-research loop reads at the start of every round. Single lineage, GPT-5.6-sol (`xhigh`, `fast`) via `cli-codex`, up to 16 rounds. Research-only: **do not run implementation, write Rust, modify backend source, or absorb phase-002 query work.**
.opencode/specs/system-code-graph/035-rust-backend-rewrite/001-research/research/deep-research-fanout-config.json:6:      "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:36:> These decisions are the frozen output of a two-lineage deep-research fan-out (GPT-5.6-SOL, GPT-5.6-LUNA) reconciled into `research/research.md`, then hardened through a three-pass verification: SOL synthesis → Fable-5 verify → GPT-5.6-SOL verify-of-Fable. Items marked **BLOCKING** are prerequisites the first implementation phase MUST satisfy before it can claim the strict invariant.
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:49:| **Deciders** | Operator; two research lineages (SOL, LUNA); three-pass verification |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:121:| **Deciders** | Operator; SOL final safety contract (stricter than LUNA's `--force-with-lease` allowance) |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:125:LUNA documented `--force-with-lease=<ref>:<expect>` as a CAS primitive and allowed bounded optimistic retry. SOL's final safety contract rejects every force-capable push form because `--force-with-lease` can authorize a non-fast-forward update, and background fetch can undermine the shorthand lease.
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:303:| 1 | GPT-5.6-SOL (max, fast) synthesis | Recommends four-plane architecture + projection-first invariant | Draft final recommendation (`research/research.md` basis) |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/decision-record.md:305:| 3 | GPT-5.6-SOL (max, fast) verify-of-Fable | AGREE-WITH-ADJUSTMENTS; do NOT freeze verbatim | Refined 3 Fable findings, promoted 2 to blocking, added 6 new blocking findings (trust boundary, projection durability, remote-policy-vs-merge-commit, sole-writer enforcement, invariant precision, edge objects); produced the 17-item directive folded into ADR-002…005 |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/spec.md:124:| REQ-006 | Compare across the research lineages. | Findings note where the SOL and LUNA lineages agree, disagree, and add unique evidence (the planned GLM lineage was dropped for safety; the reduced cross-model coverage is recorded). |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/spec.md:153:| `cli-codex` + Codex CLI (GPT-5.6 SOL/LUNA) | External executor | GPT lineages cannot run |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:3:description: "Methodology for the 137 research phase: two deep-research lineages (GPT-5.6-SOL xhigh, GPT-5.6-LUNA max), five iterations each via cli-codex, reconciled into one synthesis and hardened by a three-pass verification. A planned GLM-5.2 lineage was dropped for safety."
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:7:  - "sol luna fan-out"
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:47:| **Lineages** | Two completed (SOL, LUNA); a third (GLM) was planned and dropped for safety |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:81:| `parallel-git-sol` | GPT-5.6-SOL, effort `xhigh`, tier `fast` | `cli-codex` | `--model gpt-5.6-sol -c model_reasoning_effort="xhigh" -c service_tier="fast"` | 5 | Complete |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:82:| `parallel-git-luna` | GPT-5.6-LUNA, effort `max`, tier `fast` | `cli-codex` | `--model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="max" -c service_tier="fast"` | 5 | Complete |
.opencode/specs/sk-git/008-research-and-requirements/plan.md:148:| `cli-codex` + Codex CLI (GPT-5.6 SOL/LUNA) | External | Used | GPT lineages cannot run |
