.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:64:The recommended approach is the ordered P0-to-P4 program already ruled in `decision-record.md`. P0 makes the current flag and fallback state legible, separates drift from breakage in the harness, exposes serving status per hub, and removes or explicitly guards the resolver's dependency on a spec-tree path. P1 through P4 then add drift CI, a one-profile canary, data-driven eligibility, and a hub-by-hub global default change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:77:- [ ] The fallback, drift-CI, observability, and migration contracts in `spec.md` and `decision-record.md` are treated as authoritative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:79:- [ ] The P2 canary environment profile and promotion owner are named.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:83:- [ ] P0 through P4 acceptance evidence is recorded without changing routing decisions.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:84:- [ ] The flag is documented before any default changes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:85:- [ ] Drift is surfaced as drift, resolver breakage is surfaced as breakage, and per-hub authority is inspectable.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98:Observe, enforce, canary, derive, then cut over. Serving authority remains data-driven and fail-safe: runtime consumption is gated by the environment flag and per-hub eligibility, while a missing or stale manifest follows the legacy path defined by the authoritative contract.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:102:- **Environment contract**: documents the flag's current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:103:- **Serving-status probe**: reports `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, or `drifted` for each hub and separates expected degradation from execution failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:104:- **Drift CI**: recomputes live routing-input hashes and rejects stale manifests with a re-mint-required message.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:118:flag + serving gate ---- disabled -----> legacy path + explicit status
