.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:163:### Phase 2: Implementation (P1 and P2 enforcement)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:165:- [ ] P1: add CI that recomputes each hub's live routing-input hash and compares it with the minted manifest digest.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:166:- [ ] P1: fail with `re-mint required: <hub>` whenever a routing input changes without a matching manifest update.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:167:- [ ] P2: select one environment profile and enable compiled routing only there; keep the repository default and all other profiles off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:168:- [ ] P2: record parity, serving-status, drift, and fallback evidence for the canary.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:169:- [ ] Re-hash the frozen scorer files after P1 and P2.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:170:- [ ] Rollback: disable the drift-CI job without removing its diagnostic command; unset the canary override or set it to `0`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:172:### Phase 3: Verification and Cutover (P3 and P4)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:174:- [ ] P3: implement one data-driven eligibility predicate using the valid-fresh-manifest rule from `decision-record.md`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:175:- [ ] P3: make both existing eligibility consumers derive from that predicate, retaining the old constants as a temporary rollback path until parity is proven.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:176:- [ ] P4: change the repository default in a staged hub order, updating the two runtime predicates and each hub directive in lockstep.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:177:- [ ] P4: after every hub, require route-gold parity, a `compiled-serving` status, clean fallback behavior, and unchanged scorer hashes before proceeding.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:178:- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:179:- [ ] Rollback: stop at the first failed gate, set the flag to `0`, restore the affected hub's prior authority, and, if needed, restore the temporary hardcoded eligibility constants.
