.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Planned-state record for the P0-to-P4 compiled-routing cutover. The ruling is settled (adopt the phased path); all runtime implementation remains future work gated on an operator go-ahead to begin P0."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:6:  - "P0 P4 cutover current status"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:30:      - "Which environment profile hosts the P2 canary?"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:47:| **Status** | Ruling settled (adopt the phased path P0->P4, decided on the analysis; reversible and operator-overridable). No runtime implementation started; a separate operator go-ahead gates P0. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:60:The decision packet settles the ruling on the analysis: adopt a staged path to compiled routing as the effective default rather than flipping the default now. No runtime work has begun. The current live integration remains additive metadata only, the compiled and legacy decisions remain identical, and the repository flag remains off by default. The operator may override the ruling to flip-now at any time; that override is available but not blocking.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:62:The planned program starts by documenting and observing the existing behavior, then adds drift enforcement, a bounded canary, data-driven eligibility, and finally a reversible hub-by-hub default change. The three benchmark scorer files remain pinned throughout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:72:Document the environment flag, distinguish drift-to-legacy from resolver breakage, expose serving status per hub, and remove or explicitly guard the runtime dependency on a spec-tree path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:74:### P1 and P2: Enforcement and Canary
