.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/plan.md:204:| Setup | Stable P0/P3 interfaces | Core implementation |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:3:description: "Plan the Lane C harness changes that exercise the compiled router with SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1, compare its normalized routing decisions with legacy router replay and the same authored route gold, and classify manifest drift separately from compiled-path breakage without editing the three frozen scorer files."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:7:  - "compiled routing drift benchmark"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:18:- Scope drift, vague acceptance criteria, and optimistic done-language without evidence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:25:Lane C currently benchmarks deterministic routing through `router-replay.cjs`, joins the observed result to authored route gold, and scores it through `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`. The orchestrator never turns on `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`, never invokes the compiled front door, and never compares the compiled decision with the legacy replay. A hub can therefore pass the benchmark while the path intended to serve under the compiled flag is stale, falling back, or broken.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:27:This phase plans a harness around the frozen scorer. For each eligible hub and authored route-gold scenario, Lane C will preserve the existing legacy observation, invoke the public compiled front door in a child process with the flag set to `1`, normalize both outputs to the same routing projection, assert each against the same route gold, and require compiled-versus-legacy routing equality. Drift and no-manifest states use the classifications owned by `../012-default-on-decision/`; this packet references those contracts and does not restate them.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:52:`run-skill-benchmark.cjs` resolves a skill root, runs structural gates, loads scenarios, dispatches router-mode cases, calls `scoreScenario()`/`evaluateRouteGold()`, aggregates, and writes the JSON/Markdown reports. In deterministic Mode A, `executor-dispatch.cjs` selects `router-replay.cjs`. Hub route-gold is enforced by default, but the observed route is still the legacy replay only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:54:The existing seam is suitable for an additive parity lane: `router-replay.cjs` returns legacy intents/resources and hub telemetry; `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` returns the flag-gated compiled decision or a legacy sentinel; `score-skill-benchmark.cjs` already exports the route-gold evaluator. The missing piece is normalization and comparison around those unchanged modules.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:58:Lane C validates authored routing but not the path that will serve when compiled routing is enabled. It cannot prove that the flag-on front door actually returns a compiled decision, that the decision matches the legacy route, or that stale-manifest fallback is distinguishable from a broken compiled path. Adding compiled logic inside the scorer would corrupt the pinned baseline and mix routing observation with scoring policy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:62:Add a deterministic compiled-routing parity harness, integrate its structured result into Lane C reporting and process gates, and cover fresh, drifted, missing, and broken fixture states. The three frozen scorer files remain byte-identical and are consumed read-only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:73:- Child-process invocation of `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` for eligible hubs so the real public flag-gated path is exercised.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:78:- Drift classification, re-mint-required reporting, and hard-failure classification through the status contract owned by the decision packet.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:83:- Editing the frozen files `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, or `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:84:- Changing D1-D5 weights, route-gold semantics, scenario loading, authored gold, routing decisions, or manifest contents.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:87:- Generating or re-minting production manifests during a benchmark run. Drift is reported, never repaired automatically.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:95:3. `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:99:For each route-gold scenario on a valid fresh eligible hub:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:103:3. Reject a legacy sentinel as either `drifted` or `broken` using the shared status probe; do not guess from the sentinel alone.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:114:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/run-skill-benchmark.cjs` | Modify | Run the parity lane for eligible hub scenarios, gate the verdict, and preserve current scoring |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:117:| `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/tests/compiled-routing-parity.vitest.ts` | Create | Cover fresh parity, divergence, drift, no-manifest, breakage, and env isolation |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:133:| REQ-002 | Exercise the real compiled-serving path with the flag on. | Eligible hub scenarios invoke `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` in a child process with `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1`; the report records `flagForcedOn: true` and the front-door outcome. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:134:| REQ-003 | Require route-gold success and routing equality for compiled and legacy observations. | Both projected observations pass the same authored route gold and their normalized routing projections compare equal; a mismatch names scenario, legacy projection, compiled projection, and first differing field. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:135:| REQ-004 | Distinguish manifest drift, legacy-by-construction, and compiled breakage. | Status comes from the shared decision-contract probe: no manifest records legacy-only; stale manifest records drift and re-mint-required; fresh manifest plus resolver/front-door failure records breakage. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:136:| REQ-005 | Integrate parity as a Lane C gate without changing D1-D5. | `report.compiledRouting` contains mode, eligible rows, parity counts, drift rows, breakages, and frozen hashes; routing divergence or breakage produces a distinct blocked verdict and non-zero exit, while drift remains visibly classified according to the authoritative contract. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:139:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:143:| REQ-007 | Cover the full state matrix with deterministic fixtures. | Vitest covers fresh parity, forced divergence, stale manifest, missing manifest, malformed/fresh breakage, explicit flag isolation, and frozen-file hash drift detection. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:152:- **SC-001**: Every eligible route-gold row exercises the public flag-on compiled front door.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:155:- **SC-004**: Drift, missing-manifest legacy, and fresh-manifest breakage are reported as different states using the authoritative shared classifier.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:168:| Dependency | P3 eligibility predicate and manifest discovery | Harness cannot know whether to expect compiled serving without it | Gate parity only through the shared predicate; no local hub list |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:170:| Risk | Harness accidentally changes scorer meaning | Existing aggregate scores drift | Add before/after legacy report fixture; keep new verdict logic in the orchestrator |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:171:| Risk | Test mutates production manifest to simulate drift | Benchmark fixture leaks into live state | Copy inputs into temp fixtures or inject path adapters; never edit live manifests |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:172:| Risk | Child env leaks into the parent test process | Later tests observe flag-on behavior | Pass a cloned env to spawn and assert parent env before/after |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:173:| Risk | Drift is mislabeled as breakage | Routine re-mint state appears as runtime failure | Use the shared status probe, not sentinel inference |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:183:- **NFR-D01**: Router-mode parity runs offline and returns identical results for identical skill, manifest, and scenario bytes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:188:- **NFR-I01**: The flag is scoped to the compiled child process only.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:189:- **NFR-I02**: All drift/breakage fixtures use temp or injected paths and leave production artifacts unchanged.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:208:### Eligibility and Serving
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:211:- Stale manifest: record drift/re-mint-required; do not report generic compiled breakage.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:213:- Flag already set in parent process: child still receives an explicit `1`, and the parent value is unchanged after the call.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:217:- Scenario without route gold: omit from the hard parity denominator or record diagnostic-only status; never fabricate gold.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:240:- Should a drifted live hub make Lane C exit non-zero directly, or should Lane C report the degraded state while the separate P1 drift-CI job owns the failing process signal? The report must distinguish drift from breakage either way.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:242:- Should the parity gate default to `auto` for valid-fresh hubs and `off/not-applicable` elsewhere, or use an explicit `--compiled-routing-parity on|off|auto` flag mirroring route-gold? The recommendation is `auto` with a recorded resolved mode.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/014-benchmark-alignment/spec.md:249:- **Fallback, eligibility, drift, and observability authority**: `../012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md`

