 succeeded in 0ms:
   185	
   186	**Decision tree** (apply in order — first match wins):
   187	
   188	| State | CODEX_OAUTH_OK | Action |
   189	|-------|----------------|--------|
   190	| OAuth ready | 1 | Proceed with `codex exec --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast"` |
   191	| Not logged in | 0 | **ASK user** to run `codex login` — surface the command, do NOT dispatch. Never substitute an API key or a different model. |
   192	
   193	**User prompt template — not logged in:**
   194	
   195	```
   196	Codex is not authenticated on this machine. cli-codex uses ChatGPT OAuth only.
   197	Run `codex login` (browser flow; requires a ChatGPT Plus/Pro/Business/Edu/Enterprise account),
   198	then confirm when login finishes — the skill will retry the original dispatch.
   199	```
   200	
   201	**Error-recovery contract.** If a dispatch returns an auth error after pre-flight passed (OAuth expired or revoked), invalidate the cache, rerun `codex login`, and re-check before retrying. Never substitute a model the user didn't approve.
   202	
   203	### Default Invocation (Skill Default)
   204	
   205	**Default model + effort + tier**: `gpt-5.5` · `medium` reasoning · `fast` service tier. Balances speed, cost, and quality for the typical delegation.
   206	
   207	```bash
   208	codex exec \
   209	  --model gpt-5.5 \
   210	  -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" \
   211	  -c service_tier="fast" \
   212	  -c approval_policy=never \
   213	  --sandbox workspace-write \
   214	  "<prompt>"
   215	```
   216	
   246	### Codex Agent Delegation
   247	
   248	The calling AI is the conductor; Codex profiles in `.codex/config.toml` `[profiles.<name>]` shape HOW Codex processes the task (sandbox, reasoning). Route with `-p <name>` when the task matches a specialization. Full roster and invocation patterns: [agent-delegation.md](./references/agent-delegation.md).
   249	
   250	| Task Type | Profile |
   251	|-----------|---------|
   252	| Code review / security audit | `review` |
   253	| Architecture exploration | `context` |
   254	| Technical research | `research` (+ top-level `--search`) |
   255	| Documentation generation | `write` |
   256	| Fresh-perspective debugging | `debug` |
   257	| Multi-strategy planning | `ai-council` |
   258	
   259	Git diff review uses the built-in subcommand (no `-p`): `codex exec review "..." --commit HEAD`. Profiles may override `model`, `model_reasoning_effort`, `sandbox_mode`, `approval_policy`. The `.codex/agents/*.toml` files define personas for the interactive multi-agent TUI, NOT the `-p` flag.
   260	
   261	### Dispatch-Critical Gotchas
   262	
   263	The full flag glossary, sandbox modes, unique capabilities (`/review`, `--search`, `codex mcp`, session resume/fork, `--image`, `codex cloud`), essential command examples, and troubleshooting table are in the ALWAYS-loaded [cli-reference.md](./references/cli-reference.md). Four gotchas that silently break a dispatch and must be honored at routing time:
   264	
   265	- **`codex exec` defaults to `--sandbox read-only`** — file-modification tasks silently no-op (the agent plans changes but cannot write them). Pass `--sandbox workspace-write` (or `--full-auto`) whenever the task requires edits.
   266	- **`--search` is a top-level flag, not an `exec` flag** — enable live web search as `codex --search exec …` (it precedes the subcommand). On codex ≥ 0.144 `codex exec --search` hard-fails with `unexpected argument '--search'` (older 0.125 builds accepted it), so treat any `exec … --search` example as stale. Without it, `codex exec` has no web access and answers from training data only — every dispatch needing live data (latest versions, repo facts, advisories) MUST use `codex --search exec …`.
   267	- **Always pass `-c service_tier="fast"` explicitly** — this routes through the fast tier instead of whatever the caller's `~/.codex/config.toml` defaults to. Explicit means reproducible regardless of who runs it.
   268	- **No `--reasoning-effort`, `--reasoning`, or `--quiet` flag exists** — set effort with `-c model_reasoning_effort="<level>"`; capture the last message with `-o file.txt`; capture stderr with `2>&1`.
   269	
   270	---
   271	
   272	## 4. RULES
   273	
   274	### ✅ ALWAYS
   275	
   276	1. Verify Codex CLI is installed before first invocation (`command -v codex`).
   277	2. Delegate orchestrated execution to `../../system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs` with executor kind `cli-codex`; never build a second adapter in this packet.
   278	3. Use `--sandbox read-only` for review/analysis/research; `--sandbox workspace-write` (or `--full-auto`) for code generation/file modification — `codex exec` defaults to `read-only`, so omitting causes silent no-op on edit tasks.
   279	4. Validate Codex-generated code (XSS, injection, eval, syntax checks via `node --check`, `tsc --noEmit`, etc.) before applying.
   280	5. Capture stderr (`2>&1`) so rate-limit messages and errors surface.
   281	6. **Redirect codex stdin from `/dev/null`** when dispatching in a `while read` loop. Pattern: `codex exec "$PROMPT" > "$LOG" 2>&1 </dev/null &`. Without `</dev/null`, the backgrounded codex process inherits the loop's stdin (the file after `done < input.jsonl`) and silently consumes the remaining lines — the loop exits after 3-6 iterations with no error. See `references/integration-patterns.md#background-execution` → "Silent Stdin Consumption".
   282	7. **Specify model + effort + service tier explicitly** — never rely on caller environment. Default: `--model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast"`. Honor user overrides verbatim. Use `high`/`xhigh` for reasoning-heavy tasks (architecture, security, deep planning).
   283	8. Route to the appropriate `-p <profile>` when the task matches a specialization (see Section 3 routing table); use `codex exec review` (built-in subcommand) for git diff reviews.
   284	9. **Pass the spec folder to the delegated agent** in the prompt: if the calling AI has an active Gate-3 spec folder, include `Spec folder: <path> (pre-approved, skip Gate 3)`. If none, ASK the user before delegating — the delegated agent cannot answer Gate 3 in `--full-auto` or non-interactive mode.
   285	10. **Prompt construction & model-craft (cli-* family precedence).** Compose every dispatch prompt via the 3-tier rule canonical in `../../sk-prompt/prompt-models/assets/cli-prompt-quality-card.md`:

