codex
The placement boundary is now clear: the seven compiled-eligible hub roots own hub-routing scenarios; their child-mode playbooks do not. The advisor’s own playbook must separately own envelope, fallback, and serving-state behavior. One additional issue surfaced: the normal hook/brief path appears not to consume the additive `compiledRoute` field, so a model-run scenario could “pass” on legacy instructions while never exercising the compiled decision. I’m tracing that handoff before finalizing the matrix.
