     9	<!-- sk-doc-template: manual_testing_playbook -->
    10	
    11	This document combines the canonical manual-validation contract for the `skill_advisor` package into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the operator directory, review protocol and orchestration guide while the per-feature files carry scenario-specific execution truth.
    12	
    13	---
    14	
    15	This playbook package follows the sk-doc manual testing playbook template. The current corpus is the historical operator scenario set merged into the canonical manual-testing package on 2026-05-07, with former `SAD-NNN` scenarios absorbed into their current `NC` and `CL` homes.
    16	
    17	Canonical package artifacts:
    18	- `manual-testing-playbook.md`
    19	- `native-mcp-tools/`
    20	- `cli-hooks-and-plugin/`
    21	- `compat-and-disable/`
    22	- `operator-h5/`
    23	- `auto-update-daemon/`
    24	- `auto-indexing/`
    25	- `lifecycle-routing/`
    26	- `scorer-fusion/`
    27	- `python-compat/`
    28	
    29	---
    30	
    31	## 1. OVERVIEW
    32	
    33	This playbook provides 47 deterministic scenario files across 9 categories validating the Skill Advisor surface. Scenario IDs use a multi-prefix scheme: `NC` for native MCP tools, `CL` for CLI hooks plus plugin behavior, `CP` for compatibility plus disable controls, `OP` for operator H5 states, `AU` for auto-update daemon behavior, `AI` for auto-indexing, `LC` for lifecycle routing, `SC` for scorer fusion, plus `PC` for Python compatibility.
    34	
    35	> **Numbering note (gap-09).** The directory layout skips slot `09--*` between `scorer-fusion` and `python-compat`. This mirrors the `feature-catalog/` 05-gap pattern and is an intentional historical reservation from initial scaffold design. The gap is preserved to keep spec-folder cross-reference stability across packets. Do not renumber.
    36	
    37	Coverage note (2026-05-07): the prior operator scenario corpus now lives under `manual-testing-playbook/` as the canonical manual validation package. Former `SAD-NNN` IDs are deprecated plus mapped to current feature files in section 18. The source root index describes 42 scenarios, but the source category tree contains 41 `NNN-*.md` scenario files plus no `CL-002`. This root playbook reflects the live file inventory.
    38	
    39	### Realistic Test Model
    40	
    41	1. A realistic user request is given to an operator or runtime.
    42	2. The operator decides whether to call the native MCP tool, run a prompt-time hook, execute compatibility shims or inspect daemon/indexing behavior.
    43	3. The operator captures command transcripts, MCP envelopes, hook stdout/stderr and final verdicts.
    44	4. The scenario passes only when observed output is prompt-safe, user-visible and consistent with the documented feature contract.
    45	
    64	```
    65	
    66	4. `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED` is unset unless a scenario explicitly sets it.
    67	5. Operators can call Skill Advisor MCP tools or run the documented Node/Python commands from the repo root.
    68	6. Destructive or stateful scenarios use a disposable workspace copy unless the scenario explicitly validates the live checkout.
    69	
    70	---
    71	
    72	## 3. GLOBAL EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS
    73	
    74	- Scenario ID and per-feature file path.
    75	- User request or operational condition used.
    76	- Exact command transcript or MCP call payload.
    77	- Full JSON output or a focused excerpt containing asserted fields.
    78	- Exit code for shell commands.
    79	- Hook stdout and stderr captured separately when hook scripts are involved.
    80	- Final user-facing verdict with rationale.
    81	- Triage notes for every `FAIL`, `PARTIAL` or `SKIP`.
    82	
    83	---
    84	
    85	## 4. DETERMINISTIC COMMAND NOTATION
    86	
    87	- CLI commands shown as `bash: <command>`.
    88	- MCP tool calls shown as `advisor_recommend({ key: value })` or the named advisor tool call.
    89	- Hook stdin payloads shown as JSON piped into the compiled hook script.
    90	- `->` separates sequential steps inside one scenario contract.
    91	- File references use repo-root-relative paths unless otherwise stated.
    92	
